fields.name: Slumber Party Panic
fields.overview: Finn and Princess Bubblegum must protect the Candy Kingdom from a horde of candy zombies they accidentally created.

fields.name: Trouble in Lumpy Space
fields.overview: Finn must travel to Lumpy Space to find a cure that will save Jake, who was accidentally bitten by Lumpy Space Princess at a tea party.

fields.name: Prisoners of Love
fields.overview: When the Ice King kidnaps a number of princesses he sees as potential brides, Finn and Jake team with the prisoners to set everybody free.

fields.name: Tree Trunks
fields.overview: Finn and Jake join Tree Trunks in search for the rare Crystal Gem Apple, but question whether Tree Trunks has what it takes to adventure.

fields.name: The Enchiridion!
fields.overview: Finn and Jake go on a quest for a magical book that would prove them worthy of being righteous heroes.

fields.name: The Jiggler
fields.overview: A jiggly creature attracted by Finn's auto-tuned singing follows Finn and Jake home but soon feels ill effects of separation from its family.

fields.name: Ricardio the Heart Guy
fields.overview: When a Heart Guy named Ricardio comes to Candy Kingdom, Finn gets really jealous and finds a way to get him out of the Land of Ooo.

fields.name: Business Time
fields.overview: When Finn and Jake discover a group of businessmen frozen in an iceberg, the duo thaws them and hires them to help with their adventures.

fields.name: My Two Favorite People
fields.overview: Jake's plan to spend time with both Lady Rainicorn and Finn backfires.

fields.name: Memories of Boom Boom Mountain
fields.overview: Finn reflects on an upsetting experience in his past and pledges to help everyone in town, but this proves more difficult than imagined.

fields.name: Wizard
fields.overview: Finn and Jake temporarily get magic powers from an evil wizard, but are tricked into helping stop a comet.

fields.name: Evicted!
fields.overview: Finn and Jake search the land of Ooo for a new home after Marceline claims the duo's treehouse as her own.

fields.name: City of Thieves
fields.overview: Finn and Jake go off to face a thief king who has been stealing from little girls.

fields.name: The Witch's Garden
fields.overview: Finn and Jake consider breaking up after a witch strips Jake of his powers.

fields.name: What Is Life?
fields.overview: Finn brings a pie-throwing robot to life, but the machine begins to long for a more fulfilling existence.

fields.name: Ocean of Fear
fields.overview: Finn struggles to overcome his fear of the ocean.

fields.name: When Wedding Bells Thaw
fields.overview: The Ice King gets married but not before he convinces Finn and Jake to throw him a manlorette party.

fields.name: Dungeon
fields.overview: Finn's headstrong decision to explore a dungeon in defiance of Jake's warnings leads to a dangerous escapade.

fields.name: The Duke
fields.overview: Finn must tell the truth when he accidentally turns Princess Bubblegum bald and green and blames the Duke of Nuts.

fields.name: Freak City
fields.overview: After being transformed into a foot, Finn joins forces with a band of misfits to make things right.

fields.name: Donny
fields.overview: Finn and Jake try to help an obnoxious grass ogre named Donny develop better social skills, only to find out Donny's jerky behavior protects the house people from the why-wolves, which eat the house people.

fields.name: Henchman
fields.overview: After seeing Marceline the vampire queen torment an elderly henchman, Finn steps in to be her new henchman, doing whatever he is told to do.

fields.name: Rainy Day Daydream
fields.overview: Stuck inside the treehouse due to a knife storm, Finn and Jake use their imagination to pass the time.

fields.name: What Have You Done?
fields.overview: Finn and Jake capture the Ice King as their prisoner, but feel guilty when unable to explain the wrongs he committed.

fields.name: His Hero
fields.overview: The great warrior Billy inspires Finn and Jake to practice nonviolence, but the duo finds it difficult to resist old ways.

fields.name: Gut Grinder
fields.overview: When the Fluffy People's gold has been devoured by a culprit only known as "The Gut Grinder", Finn and Jake team up to find him with his tracks.
